'''Hetu Bhardwaj''' (Hoti Lal Bhardwaj) is an [[India]]n [[Hindi]] fiction writer. Dr Bhardwaj writes in contemporary genre of the language, and has published more than 20 novels/ short stories collections so far. Dr Bhardwaj was awarded the [[Sahitya Akademi Award|Rajasthan Sahitya Academy Award]] in 1980, and again in 1993.

Some of his best works include ''Teen Kamron Ka Makan'', ''Chief Sahab Aa Rahey Hain'', "''Chhupane Ko Chhupa Jaata'', "''Banti Bigarti Lakeeren'', ''Teerth Yatra''.

Born in Ramner, [[Bulandshahar]], [[Uttar Pradesh|UP]] on 15.1.1937, Dr Bhardwaj obtained his MA in [[Hindi literature|Hindi Literature]] in 1960 from [[Rajasthan University]], [[Jaipur]]. He received his PhD in Hindi Literature in 1981, also from Rajasthan University. He retired as Principal, Government College, [[Neem-Ka-Thana]], District [[Sikar district|Sikar]], [Rajasthan], and now spends his time in freelance writing, and taking care of his family at Chhaoni, Neem-Ka-Thana, and at Jaipur.

'''References:'''
1. Who's Who of Indian Writers by KC Dutt, ''Sahitya Akademi'' <ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=QA1V7sICaIwC&pg=PA140&lpg=PA140&dq=hetu+bhardwaj&source=web&ots=iZla82XSJe&sig=F2kzQFPsm8ldq6R_Pbb9czy5fhU&hl=en</ref>

