{{Infobox language |name=Turumsa |nativename= |region=[[Papua New Guinea]] |speakers=5 |date=2002 |ref=e18 |speakers2=possibly extinct (2011) |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Papuan Gulf languages|Papuan Gulf]] ? |fam2=Strickland |fam3=[[Doso–Turumsa languages|Doso–Turumsa]] |iso3=tqm |glotto=turu1250 |glottorefname=Turumsa }}
'''Turumsa''' is a possibly extinct [[Papuan language]] of [[Papua New Guinea]]. It has been classified as a [[Bosavi languages|Bosavi language]], and is 19% lexically similar with the Bosavi language [[Dibiyaso language|Dibiyaso]], but this appears to be due to loans. It has a greater (61%) lexical similarity with [[Doso language|Doso]], its only clear relative.<ref name="Glottolog" />
